The Africa Centres for Disease Control and Prevention (Africa CDC) says there are now 6,213 confirmed cases of Coronavirus (COVID-19) in 49 countries across Africa. The health agency disclosed this in a tweet on its official Twitter account on Thursday morning. According to the tweet, COVID-19 had killed 221 people in Africa, while a total of 469 patients recovered from the disease across the continent. ”COVID19 – Surveillance update in Africa: 2 APRIL 2020 – 9:00 am EAT,” Africa CDC tweeted. ”African Union Member States (49) reporting 6,213 COVID-19 cases, 221 deaths, and 469 recoveries by region.” DAILY POST recalls that Africa CDC had also provided an update on Coronavirus on Wednesday. 